Failure and recovery logic
This should be one of the most important site rules because it closes the gap between ideal planning and real behavior. You asked for incentives and failure conditions, but the system needs recovery logic too or users will abandon it after a bad week.
•	Missing a task does not erase past XP
•	Missed recurring tasks become Recovery Missions
•	Three missed tasks in one domain trigger a Backlog Triage Mission
•	Two broken streaks in one week trigger Overwhelm Reset Protocol
•	Elite tasks can be downgraded into 3–5 smaller missions
•	Recovery missions award lower XP than original missions, but restore momentum
•	“Win the day” = complete 1 important mission, 1 ritual, and 1 documentation action
