What should be separated
I’d break the project into more granular files so each part has one job only. That matches your goal of swapping task content without touching the core engine and helps keep the Akatsuki RPG system stable as it grows.
Recommended file structure
•	index.html — layout only, no content data.
•	style.css — all styling and Akatsuki theme tokens.
•	script.js — game engine, state, UI wiring, localStorage, reset logic.
•	game-data.json — global rules, XP rules, coin rules, achievements, avatar/shop rules.
•	task-bank.json — master task data only.
•	task-bank-phd.json — PhD missions only.
•	task-bank-skool.json — Skool/community missions only.
•	task-bank-curriculum.json — curriculum missions only.
•	task-bank-ra.json — research assistantship missions only.
•	task-bank-docs.json — documentation missions only.
•	task-bank-rituals.json — rituals, reset, daily discipline missions only.
•	boss-battles.json — all boss missions only.
•	recovery-missions.json — all recovery / reset missions only.
•	mini-quests.json — tiny low-friction momentum missions only.
•	achievements.json — badges and unlock conditions only.
•	shop-items.json — cosmetics, bonuses, gear only.
•	mission-templates.json — reusable templates for generated tasks.
•	mission-tags.json — priority, energy, context, domain, and mission type lists.
•	avatar-layers.json — SVG layer definitions, defaults, and unlockable parts.
This separation gives you a real content system, not just one giant bank. It also makes it easy to swap a single domain, like your PhD tasks, without disturbing the rest of the app.
